x4freetext: Data for 197Au, 232Th and 238U
Experimental procedures given.
Survey of Tritium-Producing Nuclear Reactions
The foil stacks served to determine the distribution
of tritium produced in the targets. Due to the long
range of tritons in the beam direction, the tritium
detected in a specific foil may originate from
previous foils. Thus, only an `apparent` excitation
function is measured.
Tritium extracted by heating foils in a measured amount
of hydrogen carrier followed by selective diffusion of
hydrogen isotopes through a palladium thimble and
introduction into a counter tube.
Methane-filled proportional counter.
`Apparent` cross sections calculated on the basis of
thin-target approximations as if the beam were
incident on each foil in which tritons were detected.
These cross sections were summed over total foil depth
to give triton yield per incident particle.
According to spectroscopic analyses, impurities in the
target foils were found to be negligible.
